Vrbas (Врбас) is a city located in Serbia and Montenegro at 45.57° North, 19.65° East. Its name stems from word "Willow" in the Serbian language. In 2002, the city had a total population of 25,887.

Vrbas is also a river in central Bosnia and Herzegovina. It is a tributary of the Sava River. The town of Banja Luka is located on the river banks. This was also the name of one of the banovine of the Kingdom of Yugoslavia.

